<header>
  <h1>Digital Twin Platform for Bangladesh</h1>
  <p>Empowering Citizens with Justice, Memory, and Safe Voice</p>
</header>

<section>
  <h2>Concept</h2>
  <p>
    A unified digital platform merging governance, legal literacy, local history, and AI-shielded anonymous reporting for Bangladeshi communities.
  </p>

  <h2>Key Features</h2>
  <div class="feature">
    <strong>1. Digital Community Map:</strong> Interactive 3D maps of villages/towns showing offices, schools, roads, and public spaces.
    <div class="map-placeholder">[3D Map Placeholder]</div>
  </div>
  <div class="feature">
    <strong>2. AI Legal Comics:</strong> Visual & audio stories in Bangla teaching citizens their rights and justice processes.
  </div>
  <div class="feature">
    <strong>3. Living History Archive:</strong> Capture and visualize local governance events, cultural heritage, and justice struggles.
  </div>
  <div class="feature">
    <strong>4. Anonymous Reporting:</strong> AI-powered anonymization for safe reporting of corruption and injustice.
  </div>

  <h2>Innovation & Uniqueness</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>First platform to combine legal access, community participation, history preservation, and safe whistleblowing.</li>
    <li>Overcomes literacy barriers with visual storytelling.</li>
    <li>Globally novel, scalable, and deeply Bangladesh-specific.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Impact</h2>
  <p><strong>Short-term:</strong> Educates citizens, improves governance engagement, ensures safe reporting.</p>
  <p><strong>Long-term:</strong> Strengthens trust in institutions, creates a nationwide historical archive, and positions Bangladesh as a civic-tech leader.</p>

  <h2>Scalability</h2>
  <p>
    Pilot in one Union Parishad → expand district-by-district → nationwide. Supported by NGOs, government initiatives, and donor funding.
  </p>

  <div class="tagline">“Empowering citizens with justice, memory, and safe voice.”</div>
</section>

